A belt is drawn tightly around three circles of radius $10$ cm each, as shown. The length of the belt, in cm, can be written in the form $a + b\pi$ for rational numbers $a$ and $b$. What is the value of $a + b$? [asy]

size(120); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
picture p; real r = 3^.5/2;
pair A = expi(-pi/6); draw(p, circle(A, r)); draw(p, (A.x,A.y - r) -- (-A.x,A.y - r));
add(p); add(rotate(120)*p); add(rotate(240)*p);
[/asy]

Triangle $DEF$ is shown.  What is $\cos{E}$?

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(7,0)--(7,24)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
draw(rightanglemark((0,0),(7,0),(7,24),30),black+linewidth(1));
label("$E$",(7,24),E);
label("$F$",(0,0),W);
label("$D$",(7,0),E);
label("7",(0,0)--(7,0),S);
label("24",(7,0)--(7,24),E);
[/asy]

Squares $ABCD$ and $EFGH$ are equal in area.  Vertices $B$, $E$, $C$, and $H$ lie on the same line.  Diagonal $AC$ is extended to $J$, the midpoint of $GH$.  What is the fraction of the two squares that is shaded? [asy]
fill((0,4)--(4,4)--(4,0)--cycle,gray);
fill((4,0)--(6,0)--(6,-2)--cycle,gray);
draw((0,0)--(4,0)--(4,4)--(0,4)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((2,0)--(6,0)--(6,-4)--(2,-4)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((0,4)--(6,-2),linewidth(1));
label("$A$",(0,4),NW);
label("$B$",(0,0),W);
label("$C$",(4,0),NE);
label("$D$",(4,4),NE);
label("$E$",(2,0),SW);
label("$F$",(2,-4),SW);
label("$G$",(6,-4),SE);
label("$H$",(6,0),E);
label("$J$",(6,-2),E);
[/asy]

